Kestral::

She dreamed of moon swept shores of an ocean somewhere.  The waters
were black at night, but calm.  The sand under her feet still felt
warm from the day's heat.  Trees swayed in the light breeze that blew
off the ocean.  She looked around the beautiful place.  She was alone,
but it didn't seem to matter. She felt happy just being there.
